Individual Plots: Example of Far Northern California

  • Counties located on the right side of the plot has more disparate outcomes across race and ethnic groups than those on the left side.

  • Note that the y-axis is relative to the range of values in the region (y-axis can also be fixed, but the relative y-axis makes it easier to see within-region differences).

Plot of Existing + Expanded Regions

  • Counties located on the right side of the plot has more disparate outcomes across race and ethnic groups than those on the left side.

  • The color of the county indicates whether it is a current HPI County or a proposed new HPI county.
